     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce22"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce61" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce65"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce69"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce36"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce40"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro10">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce9"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce14" table:number-columns-repeated="4"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce23" table:number-columns-repeated="5"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce14" table:number-columns-repeated="3"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce87"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce23"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce89"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro11">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>019</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.1.1 (p. 7)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>Any revisions to specification documents shall be recorded in the revision history, along with the description</text:p><text:p>of the changes or additions made. The CHAdeMO control protocol number is assigned to manage software</text:p><text:p>compatibility between charger and vehicle developed under different specification versions.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Protocol number and changing protocol in case of the different versions</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce54" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not complete</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce61" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Software is only responsible for assigning version number and managing compatiblity between charger and vehicle</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce65"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce69"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce36"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce40"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro5">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>020</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.2 (p. 7)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>Vehicle coupler shall conform to IEC 62196-3 Standard sheets for configuration “AA.” Shapes and</text:p><text:p>dimensions of the vehicle coupler in A.17 are given for information only.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce24" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Vehicle coupler</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce45" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Out of Scope </text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce22"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce59" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not a responsibility of software</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce63"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce67"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce36"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce40"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro8">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>021</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.3 (p. 7)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>The manufacturer shall manufacture the charger with a design that conforms to the following:</text:p><text:p>a) Standard usage conditions as shown in Table A.1</text:p><text:p>b) Panel-related specifications as shown in Table A.2</text:p><text:p>c) Device specifications as shown in Table A.3 7</text:p><text:p>d) Design specifications as shown in Table A.4</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce24" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Installation conditions and main specifications</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce52" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Revision required</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce59" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p><text:span text:style-name="T3">Buttons in table A.4 might be reflected in software</text:span></text:p><text:p/><text:p><text:span text:style-name="T3">TODO verify by tests</text:span></text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce63"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce67"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce36"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce40"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro11">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>022</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.1 (p. 9)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>Constant current charging method is used for charging. The vehicle shall transmit a charging current</text:p><text:p>request to the charger at a constant time interval. The charger shall output current that corresponds to the</text:p><text:p>order value. If the order value from the vehicle changes, the charger shall vary output current that follows</text:p><text:p>the new value.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Charging method</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce54" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not complete</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce59" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce63"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce67"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce36"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce40"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro5">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>023</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.2 (p. 10)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>Dedicated control signal lines shall be used to transmit signals concerning the start and termination of</text:p><text:p>Charging.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Control signal line</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce52" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Revision required</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce58" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p><text:span text:style-name="T3">Control signal lines are not part of software, but may be implemented virtually</text:span></text:p><text:p/><text:p><text:span text:style-name="T3">TODO verify by tests</text:span></text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce62"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce66"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>see implementation of:</text:p><text:p>struct chademo_se_vgpio</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce35"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce39"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro5">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>024</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.3 (p. 10)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>A data circuit shall be used to transmit parameters required for charging control. The charger and vehicle</text:p><text:p>shall exchange the parameters through the circuit.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Data communications</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce52" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Revision required</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce58" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>Data circuit is not a part of the software itself. But parameter exchange is</text:p><text:p/><text:p>TODO verify by tests</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce62"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce66"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>Initial exchange is present at state:</text:p><text:p>_CHADEMO_SE_STATE_CF_AWAIT_CAN_RX_AND_START_TX_AFTER</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce35"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce39"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro4">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>025</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.4 a (p. 10)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>Both the charger and the vehicle shall be equipped</text:p><text:p>with a means to confirm that they stay connected with each other during charging.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Connection confirmation (Proximity detection)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce54" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not complete</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce58" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce62"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce66"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce35"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce39"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro7">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>026</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.4 b.1 (p. 10)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p> The charger shall be equipped with a means to stop charging immediately in the case that</text:p><text:p>communication between the vehicle and the charger (via the control signal lines or data</text:p><text:p>communication lines) is interrupted.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce28" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Power supply shutdown upon communications disruption</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce54" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not complete</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce58" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce62"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce66"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce35"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce39"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro7">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>027</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.4 b.2 (p. 10)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>In addition to data communication, there shall be a means that the vehicle instructs the</text:p><text:p>charger to stop charging. When the vehicle detects disruption of data communication, the</text:p><text:p>charger shall be notified to stop charging by the means.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce54" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not complete</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce58" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce62"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce66"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce35"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce39"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro5">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>028</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.4 b (p. 10)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p><text:span text:style-name="T3">The vehicle shall be equipped with a means</text:span></text:p><text:p><text:span text:style-name="T3">to prevent drive the vehicle while it is connected to the charger (whether it is before and during</text:span></text:p><text:p><text:span text:style-name="T3">Charging).</text:span></text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Prevention of false-drive (requirement for the vehicle)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce45" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Out of Scope </text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce22"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce59" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not a responsibility of software</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce63"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce67"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce35"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce39"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro7">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>029</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.4 c (p. 10)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>When the protective conductor between the charger and the vehicle is disconnected,</text:p><text:p>the charger shall stop charging immediately.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>Detection of protective conductor disconnection between charger and vehicle and charging</text:p><text:p>Termination</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce54" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not complete</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce58" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce62"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce66"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce35"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce39"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro12">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>030</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.4 d (p. 10)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>During charging, the charger shall</text:p><text:p>detect any earth fault on the dc power circuit. In the event that earth fault is detected in the dc</text:p><text:p>power circuit, the charger shall stop applying dc voltage or supplying dc current to the charging</text:p><text:p>cable. If equipped, the on-board fault detection of the vehicle shall not interfere with the earth fault</text:p><text:p>detection capability of the dc charger.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Detection and protection of earth fault on the dc power circuit</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce54" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not complete</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce58" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce62"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce66"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce35"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce39"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro6">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>031</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.4 e (p. 10)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>The charger shall be equipped with a short circuit protection function.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>DC short circuit protection</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce54" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not complete</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce58" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce62"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce66"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce35"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce39"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro2">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>032</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.4 f (p. 10)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>The charger shall be equipped with an overvoltage</text:p><text:p>protection function on vehicle systems.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Prevention of overvoltage on on-board systems</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce54" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not complete</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce58" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce62"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce66"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce35"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce39"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro4">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>033</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.4 g (p. 10)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>The vehicle shall have contactors with sufficient capacity to</text:p><text:p>break charge current.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Charge current interruption function</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce45" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Out of Scope </text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce22"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce59" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not a responsibility of software</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce63"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce67"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce35"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce39"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro13">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>034</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.4 h (p. 10)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>To protect the EV contactor, the charger shall follow the procedure in item 1), 2), and 3) of this</text:p><text:p>subclause when stopping the power supply to the control relay of the EV contactor. This procedure</text:p><text:p>shall be observed even in the event of ac input power blackout or voltage drop of ac input power.</text:p><text:p>See A.7.2.8.</text:p><text:p>Procedure for stopping the control power supply (power supply to the EV contactor)</text:p><text:p>1)</text:p><text:p> Stop the charging current.</text:p><text:p>2)</text:p><text:p> Stop the power supply to the control relay of the EV contactor.</text:p><text:p>3)</text:p><text:p> Open the EV contractor.</text:p><text:p>The charger shall have welding detection capability for monitoring the EV contactor. See A.10.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Protection of EV contactor</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce54" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not complete</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce58" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce62"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce66"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce22" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce35"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce39"/>
     <table:table-cell/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce17" table:number-columns-repeated="16367"/>
    </table:table-row>
    <table:table-row table:style-name="ro11">
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce8" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>035</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce15" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string">
      <text:p>A.4.4 i (p. 11)</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce18" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"><text:p>The stop signals from the vehicle to the</text:p><text:p>charger shall be redundant. Charging processes shall be stopped in the event that analog signal or</text:p><text:p>CAN data signal calls for the “stop” state. The charger shall be equipped with a mechanism to</text:p><text:p>ensure terminating operation according to stop request from the vehicle.</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:number-columns-repeated="2" table:style-name="ce18"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce31" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Design of hardware associated with the stop signals</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce34"/>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce38"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce54" office:value-type="string" calcext:value-type="string" table:number-columns-spanned="2" table:number-rows-spanned="1">
      <text:p>Not complete</text:p>
     </table:table-cell>
     <table:covered-table-cell table:style-name="ce54"/>
     <table:table-cell table:style-name="ce58" table:number-columns-spanned="3" table:number-rows-spanned="1"/>
